RIYADH: Ukraine’s president Volodymyr Zelensky received Saudi Arabia’s Foreign Minister Prince Faisal bin Farhan in Kyiv on Sunday. During the visit, Prince Faisal said the Kingdom is working with Ukraine to mitigate the effects of the crisis in the country economically. He added that he was discussing opportunities for continued investment cooperation with the war-torn country. “We continue to discuss opportunities to settle the crisis with all parties,” the Kingdom’s foreign minister said.